@startuml
title POST /api/v1/enrollments — Join Course (201 Created)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "join_course\n_with_code()" as View
participant "IsAuthenticated" as Auth
participant "primary_role()" as RoleCheck
participant "StudentJoinCourse\nSerializer" as Serializer
participant "redeem_student\n_join_course()" as Redeem
participant "_ensure_student\n_enrollment()" as Enroll
database Postgres

Client -> View: POST /enrollments\n{code: "REG-abc123..."}\n[Authorization: Bearer JWT]
View -> Auth: check JWT token
Auth -> Postgres: SELECT app_users WHERE id = ?
Postgres --> Auth: User
Auth --> View: request.user authenticated

View -> RoleCheck: primary_role(request.user)
RoleCheck -> Postgres: SELECT user_roles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> RoleCheck: [STUDENT]
RoleCheck --> View: "STUDENT"
View -> View: role == STUDENT? Yes

View -> Serializer: is_valid(raise_exception=True)
Serializer --> View: validated {code}

== @transaction.atomic ==

View -> Redeem: redeem_student_join_course(\nuser, code)
Redeem -> Redeem: verify primary_role == STUDENT

Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ? FOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: RegistrationCode (locked)
Redeem -> Redeem: validate code_type == STUDENT
Redeem -> Redeem: validate course_id exists
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT courses WHERE id = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: Course

Redeem -> Enroll: _ensure_student_enrollment(user, course)
Enroll -> Postgres: SELECT student_profiles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> Enroll: StudentProfile
Enroll -> Postgres: SELECT enrollments\nWHERE course_id = ?\nAND student_profile_id = ?
Postgres --> Enroll: NULL (not enrolled yet)
Enroll -> Postgres: INSERT INTO enrollments\n(course, student_profile, status=ACTIVE)
Enroll --> Redeem: (Enrollment, already=False)

Redeem -> Postgres: UPDATE registration_codes\nSET times_used += 1
Redeem --> View: (Enrollment, already=False)

== end transaction ==

View --> Client: 201 Created\n{message: "Invite redeemed",\nusername, name, courseId,\ncreatedNewUser: false,\nalreadyEnrolled: false}
@enduml
